&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Company Overview&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;x_elementToProof&quot; data-olk-copy-source=&quot;MessageBody&quot;&gt;Immunome is a clinical-stage targeted oncology company committed to developing first-in-class and best-in-class targeted cancer therapies. We are advancing an innovative portfolio of therapeutics, supported by a leadership team with deep experience in the design, development, and commercialization of cutting-edge therapies, including antibody-drug conjugates. Our pipeline includes varegacestat, an investigational gamma secretase inhibitor for which an NDA has been submitted to the U.S. FDA; IM-1021, a clinical-stage ROR1 ADC; IM-3050, an IND-cleared FAP-targeted radiotherapy; and IM-1617, an IND-cleared solid tumor ADC. We are also advancing a broad portfolio of early-stage ADCs pursuing undisclosed solid tumor targets.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Position Overview&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Contract Senior Recruiter, Life Sciences will support Immunome’s growing Clinical/Development and Commercial organizations by leading full-cycle recruitment for a broad range of roles across the organization. This position will partner closely with a variety of teams to attract, assess, and hire high-quality talent in a competitive oncology biotech environment. Solid demonstrated candidate sourcing experience is required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate is a proactive, detail-oriented recruiter with experience supporting clinical-stage life sciences organizations and managing multiple complex requisitions simultaneously.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead full-cycle recruitment for a variety of clinical and development-focused roles, including sourcing, screening, interviewing, and offer coordination.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner closely with hiring managers and HR to understand evolving business needs, role requirements, and hiring priorities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and execute proactive sourcing strategies to identify qualified candidates with experience in oncology drug development and clinical research environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct in-depth candidate interviews to assess technical qualifications, cultural fit, and alignment with Immunome’s values.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate interview logistics, gather feedback, and facilitate timely hiring decisions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure a high quality and consistent candidate experience throughout the recruitment process.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain accurate and compliant records within the applicant tracking system (Greenhouse).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide market insights related to talent availability, compensation trends, and competitive intelligence.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support contract and contingent workforce hiring needs as required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Qualifications&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree or equivalent combination of education and experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A minimum of 5 years of full-cycle recruiting experience or equivalent is required, a blend of in-house and agency experience is preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated experience recruiting Clinical/Development or Commercial focused roles within biotech, pharmaceutical, or CRO environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven ability to manage multiple requisitions in a fast-paced, high-growth environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work on-site in Bothell a minimum of one day per week.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Knowledge and Skills&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong understanding of research, clinical research, clinical development, and drug development functions within an oncology-fo

